          mock‚Äîsomething we can look at and respond to. I don‚Äôt believe in
          waiting for things to be perfect before sharing. I push for speed
          because momentum matters. I like to test ideas, prototype quickly, and
          keep moving. If something flops, cool‚Äîwe haven‚Äôt wasted weeks
          perfecting the wrong thing.</span
        >
        <span class="block"
          >This might be a leftover instinct from the tech side of me. But it‚Äôs
          also philosophical. You need to keep going to get to the good stuff.
          Jobs once said, ‚ÄúThe first solutions you come up with are very
          complex... but if you keep going and peel the layers, you get to
          something elegant.‚Äù A simple approach: build fast, learn fast, refine.
          Calculated speed and not just haste to get to mediocre results.</span
        >
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q6 -->
  <div
    class="w-full flex flex-col gap-[24px] text-[14px] font-mr font-semibold"
  >
    <hr />
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-[48px]">
      <h2 class="text-secondary">Q6: Where do you draw inspiration from?</h2>
      <p class="text-tertiary">
        <span class="block"
          >Everywhere. Conversations, old books, random UI patterns I screenshot
